│ Looking at the `LoopVectorize.cpp` file, the legacy cost model uses `getInstructionCost` to evaluate instruction costs. The VPlan cost model uses                   │
│ `VPlan.getInstructionCost`. A common source of disagreement is when one model correctly identifies an instruction as being free (e.g., foldable into another        │
│ instruction's addressing mode or a "zero-cost" operation on a specific target) while the other does not.                                                            │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
